thread.title_full: BRIEF-Warburg Pincus sells its entire stake in Poland's Amrest | Reuters

author: Reuters
title: BRIEF-Warburg Pincus sells its entire stake in Poland's Amrest
text:
July 24 Amrest Holdings Se :
* Restaurant chain Amrest said its shareholder Warburg Pincus sells its entire 32-percent stake in the company.
* Amrest did not say who would buy the stake.
* Amrest, which holds the franchises for restaurants such as Burger King, Pizza Hut and KFC, is worth 3.6 billion zlotys ($959.21 million) on the Warsaw stock exchange. Source text for Eikon: Further company coverage: ($1 = 3.7531 zlotys) (Reporting by Marcin Goclowski; Editing by Christian Lowe )
